name: Zeus In Dark Matter YIN YANG

metadata.name: Zeus In Dark Matter ( YIN_ YANG#61 )
metadata.description:
no light without darkness In general relativity, a white hole is a theoretical region of spacetime and singularity that cannot be entered from the outside, although energy-matter, light and information can escape from it. In this sense, it is the reverse of a black hole, which can be entered only from the outside and from which energy-matter, light and information cannot escape. White holes appear in the theory of eternal black holes. In addition to a black hole region in the future, such a solution of the Einstein field equations has a white hole region in its past. This region does not exist for black holes that have formed through gravitational collapse, however, nor are there any observed physical processes through which a white hole could be formed.

ZEUS CAN ENTER AND COME OUT AND HAS GIVEN THE POWER TO  HUMANS AS WELL. THINK, AND CONTROL IT.
